   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER ONE THE MEANING OF THE WORD SPIRIT</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>IN THE BIBLE AND</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>THE BASIC REVELATION</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>CONCERNING GOD AND MAN</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>IN THE HOLY SCRIPTURES Scripture Reading: Ezek.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>37:1, 5, 9; John 3:5-6; Rev 11:11; John 3:8; 4:24; Gen 1:2b; Matt 28:19b; John 14:10-11, 26; 15:26; 10:30; 8:29, 16b; 16:32b; Acts 10:38; Luke 4:1a, 18a; Gen 2:7; Prov 20:27; Zech 12:1; Isa 42:5; Job 32:8; Heb 4:12; 1 Thes 5:23a; John 4:24; 1 John 4:13; 2 Tim 4:22a; 1 Cor 6:17 OUTLINE</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Note: The general subject is not "The Spirit and Our Spirit" but "The Spirit with Our Spirit."</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>The meaning of the word spirit in the Bible: The Hebrew equivalent of the word spirit is RUACH, denoting: Spirit Ezek.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>37:1.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Breath Ezek.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>37:5.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Wind Ezek.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>37:9.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>The Greek equivalent of the word spirit is PNEUMA, denoting: Spirit John 3:5-6.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Breath Rev 11:11.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>Wind John 3:8.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>The basic revelation concerning God and man in the Holy Scriptures: Concerning God: "God is Spirit," denoting God's essence, substance John 4:24.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>"The Spirit of God," denoting that the Spirit is God Gen 1:2b.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>"The name of the Father and of the Son and of the Holy Spirit," denoting the Divine Trinity and indicating that God is triune Matt 28:19b: The three of the Divine Trinity coexist and coinhere as one God John 14:10-11, 26; 15:26; 10:30.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>They are distinct but not separate John 8:29, 16b; 16:32b; Acts 10:38; Luke 4:1a, 18a.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>Concerning man: Created by God as a tripartite man Gen 2:7: With a body formed with the dust of the ground, as man's outer frame.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>With a spirit produced of the breath of God the same Hebrew word for "breath" in Genesis 2:7 is translated into "spirit" in Proverbs 20:27 , as man's inmost organ.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>With a soul, the issue of God's breath breathed into the nostrils of the body formed of dust, as man's inner being person .</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>The spirit of man was created by God, in a particular sense, to complete God's purpose in the creation of the heavens and the earth Zech 12:1; Isa 42:5; Job 32:8.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>Man's spirit is distinct from his soul Heb 4:12; 1 Thes 5:23a.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>God is Spirit for man to contact Him and receive Him into man, and man has a spirit for man to contact God and contain God that God and man may have an organic union John 4:24; 1 John 4:13; 2 Tim 4:22a; 1 Cor 6:17.</S>
   </TEXT>
